    "id": "polymarket_event_85485",
    "title": "How high will Polymarket's mindshare go?",
    "question_type": "mcq",
    "options": [
      "80%",
      "85%",
      "75%",
      "90%",
      "70%"
    ],
    "background": "No background available.",
    "resolution_criteria": "This market will resolve to \"Yes\" if Polymarket has at least the specified daily mindshare, as shown on the Kaito Information Markets Arena page (https://kaito.ai/mindshare-arena/infomarkets) at any point between November 20, 2025, and March 31, 2026 ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to \"No\".\n\nOnly finalized daily results from the Polymarket mindshare percentage shown on the Kaito Info Markets page at https://kaito.ai/mindshare-arena/infomarkets, specifically the daily values for Polymarket under 'Historical Data', will be used to resolve this market. Values will be considered final once the value for the subsequent day has been released.\n\nThe resolution source for this market is the Kaito Info Markets page found at https://kaito.ai/mindshare-arena/infomarkets. If this resolution source is unavailable at check time, this market will remain open until the Kaito Info Markets page comes back online and resolve based on the first check after it becomes available. If it becomes permanently unavailable, this market will resolve based on the latest available data.\n\nNote: the resolution source for this market will be the Kaito Info Markets page (https://kaito.ai/mindshare-arena/infomarkets), which reports the platform’s mindshare as a percentage to two decimal places (e.g., 66.56%). Thus, this is the level of precision that will be used when resolving the market.",
    "outcome": "80%",
    "explanation": "\n# Executive Summary\nThe surge in Polymarket's mindshare to the 80% target was primarily driven by strategic partnerships, massive capital inflows, and product innovation. Initially facing fierce competition from Kalshi, which captured significant volume share via Robinhood integrations, Polymarket fought back by introducing \"mindshare\" attention markets in collaboration with Kaito AI. This novel product, combined with a record-breaking $1.4B trading month and a staggering $11.6B secondary valuation post-relaunch, generated unparalleled media buzz. The combination of these factors caused Polymarket's mindshare to decisively cross the 80% threshold.\n\n# Timeline Of Key Events\n- November 2025: Polymarket partners with Kaito AI to roll out attention markets for \"mindshare\" trading, sparking initial momentum ([art_finance_20260101_016_f944d199], [art_finance_20260101_021_e3830e64]).\n- Late November - December 2025: Kalshi briefly overtakes in volume share (up to 60%) due to a Robinhood partnership, causing market predictions for Polymarket's mindshare to dip and favor 'No' ([art_finance_20260101_006_98b94c58]).\n- January 2026: Polymarket hits a secondary valuation of $11.6B following a massive capital raise and relaunch, which led to an explosion in media coverage and retail interest ([art_finance_20260101_005_d918210e], [art_finance_20260101_020_3d9b8f53]).\n- Mid-January 2026: Despite regulatory scrutiny in Europe, Polymarket claims the mindshare lead, dominating prediction market fee share at 96.8% ([art_finance_20260101_004_9eb4f214], [art_finance_20260101_018_ef654774]).\n- February 17-18, 2026: The market decisively flips to 'Yes' as Polymarket officially hits the 80% daily mindshare threshold on the Kaito Information Markets Arena, resolving the market ([art_finance_20260101_022_a2c46e22]).\n\n# Causal Chain Analysis\nThe initial root cause was the intense competition in the prediction market space, which caused Polymarket to innovate beyond standard betting markets. This led to the intermediate mechanism of partnering with Kaito AI to create \"mindshare\" and attention-based trading markets ([art_finance_20260101_016_f944d199]). Concurrently, a massive funding round resulted in an $11.6B valuation, which triggered widespread mainstream media coverage and renewed retail interest ([art_finance_20260101_005_d918210e]). This confluence of novel product offerings and explosive valuation caused a feedback loop where traders flocked to Polymarket to trade on the very mindshare it was accumulating. The proximate trigger was the platform achieving an unprecedented 96.8% fee share dominance ([art_finance_20260101_004_9eb4f214]), which definitively pushed its daily mindshare metric past the 80% mark.\n\n# Countervailing Factors\nThe primary countervailing factor was the rise of Kalshi, a regulated US competitor. Kalshi successfully integrated with Robinhood, capturing up to 60% of the raw trading volume at one point in late 2025. Additionally, Polymarket faced regulatory crackdowns in Europe. However, these forces failed to suppress Polymarket's mindshare because mindshare (attention and cultural relevance) is distinct from raw institutional volume. Polymarket's crypto-native, globally accessible, and meme-friendly attention markets simply generated more viral engagement than Kalshi's regulated financial products.\n\n# Event Candidate Inventory\n- E1\n    - title: Polymarket and Kaito AI launch mindshare trading markets\n    - date: November 2025\n    - why it matters causally: Created the very product (attention markets) that drove retail interest.\n    - source article IDs: [art_finance_20260101_016_f944d199]\n- E2\n    - title: Kalshi achieves 60% market volume share via Robinhood\n    - date: Late 2025\n    - why it matters causally: Acted as a countervailing force that temporarily lowered expectations for Polymarket's dominance.\n    - source article IDs: [art_finance_20260101_006_98b94c58]\n- E3\n    - title: Polymarket reaches $11.6B secondary valuation post-relaunch\n    - date: January 2026\n    - why it matters causally: Triggered massive media coverage, directly spiking mindshare and user attention.\n    - source article IDs: [art_finance_20260101_005_d918210e]\n- E4\n    - title: Polymarket hits 96.8% fee share dominance\n    - date: January 2026\n    - why it matters causally: Confirmed the platform's absolute dominance in actual user willingness to pay, cementing its mindshare lead.\n    - source article IDs: [art_finance_20260101_004_9eb4f214]\n\n# Evidence Mapping Table\n| Claim/Event | Article IDs | Date Support | Confidence (0-1) | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Kaito AI partnership | [art_finance_20260101_016_f944d199] | Nov 2025 | 0.9 | Launched the mindshare markets |\n| Kalshi Robinhood volume | [art_finance_20260101_006_98b94c58] | Late 2025 | 0.9 | Countervailing competitor |\n| $11.6B valuation | [art_finance_20260101_005_d918210e] | Jan 2026 | 0.95 | Massive attention driver |\n| 96.8% fee share | [art_finance_20260101_004_9eb4f214] | Jan 2026 | 0.9 | Demonstrated actual usage dominance |\n| Hits 80% threshold | [art_finance_20260101_022_a2c46e22] | Feb 2026 | 1.0 | Resolution criteria met |\n\n# Uncertainties And Alternative Paths\nIt remains slightly uncertain exactly how much of the mindshare spike was organic versus driven by the platform's own marketing efforts and the recursive nature of users betting on mindshare. An alternative path could have seen Kalshi successfully converting its Robinhood volume into cultural mindshare, which would have kept Polymarket below the 80% threshold, but Kalshi's corporate branding failed to capture the crypto-native zeitgeist.\n",
